A ground-based time-series spectroscopic campaign contemporaneous with TESS observations is being pursued for ~200 Be stars. From spectra, the density, velocity, and temperature structure of circumstellar matter inferred. The processes leading to ejection of the disk is a key problem for Be stars, and an analysis of hundreds of such events will answer this question.
